think it's necessary.

800
01:00:31,546 --> 01:00:33,214
We know who he is.

801
01:00:33,422 --> 01:00:34,423
Who?

802
01:00:35,508 --> 01:00:36,717
Steve Adams.

803
01:00:38,302 --> 01:00:41,347
The one you called Turk
that I emailed you
about last year?

804
01:00:47,770 --> 01:00:48,771
Come on in.

805
01:00:54,735 --> 01:00:57,488
Are you afraid to look
this fella in the eye?
Let him see you?

806
01:00:57,572 --> 01:00:58,573
No.

807
01:00:59,574 --> 01:01:01,534
That's good.
I think it will
help him talk.

808
01:01:03,161 --> 01:01:04,162
(DOOR BUZZING)

809
01:01:15,756 --> 01:01:17,717
That's him,
that guy on the left.

810
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:19,218
On the far left.
That's him.

811
01:01:22,346 --> 01:01:24,307
ANDES: No,
no,no,no,no,
no. Hold up, son.

812
01:01:25,016 --> 01:01:26,559
You ain't that lucky.
Get over here.

813
01:01:26,767 --> 01:01:27,768
(CLICKS MOUTH)

814
01:01:29,520 --> 01:01:30,646
(DOOR CLOSES)

815
01:01:31,022 --> 01:01:32,273
This fella?
Yes.

816
01:01:32,356 --> 01:01:35,318
I see. Right.
I don't think
he understands.

817
01:01:35,401 --> 01:01:37,904
Lou. Lou. Hey, you.

818
01:01:39,238 --> 01:01:41,407
Your name Lou?
You know my name.
I told you.

819
01:01:41,490 --> 01:01:42,992
Yeah?
Yeah. What's going on?

820
01:01:46,204 --> 01:01:49,207
Well, I guess I want you
to tell me if you've ever
seen this man before.

821
01:01:50,082 --> 01:01:52,376
Think carefully.
You ever seen him?

822
01:01:55,004 --> 01:01:56,422
No, I don't know him.

823
01:01:56,505 --> 01:01:57,715
Hmm?
Who is he?

824
01:01:57,798 --> 01:02:00,635
Why don't you tell him, Tony?
Tell him who he is.

825
01:02:00,718 --> 01:02:02,595
Last summer, this man,
Lou, and his friends,

826
01:02:02,678 --> 01:02:04,305
